javelin.model.world.location.dungeon.temple

Class Temple

  • java.lang.Object
    • javelin.model.world.WorldActor
      • javelin.model.world.location.Location
        • javelin.model.world.location.fortification.Fortification
          • javelin.model.world.location.unique.UniqueLocation
            • javelin.model.world.location.dungeon.temple.Temple
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AirTemple, EarthTemple, EvilTemple, FireTemple, GoodTemple, MagicTemple, WaterTemple

    public abstract class Temple
extends UniqueLocation
    Temples are the key to winning Javelin. Each temple is locked and needs to be unlocked by a Key, brute Monster.strength or Skills.disabledevice. Inside the Temple there will be a Relic, and once all of those are collected they can be taken to Haxor to finish the game. Each temple is a multi-level, permanent Dungeon, where on each level can be found a ruby and the Relic sits on the last level. Battles inside temples consist of upgraded units.
    Author:
    alex
    See Also:
    Win, Haxor.rubies, TempleEncounter, Serialized Form
